Description: Two brothers harmed in a ritual that was half magic/half science seek the legendary Philosopher’s Stone to make things right.
Title: FULLMETAL ALCHEMIST, VOL. 23
Author: Hiromu Arakawa

Description: The origins and true nature of Pain, Naruto’s arch nemesis, are revealed.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 48
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Haruhi, a poor girl at a rich school, is forced to work – as a boy – for the school’s all-male club. The series is described as a “romantic comedy.”
Title: OURAN HIGH SCHOOL HOST CLUB, VOL. 14
Author: Bisco Hatori

Description: The battle for Cross Academy continues as Headmaster Cross enters the fray.
Title: VAMPIRE KNIGHT, VOL. 10
Author: Matsuri Hino

Description:
Alice wanders into a very different part of Wonderland in this interpretation of the classic tale. 

In this new area of the fantasy land, every man is in love with Alice... and firearms.
Title: ALICE IN THE COUNTRY OF HEARTS: THE CLOCKMAKER'S STORY
Author: Quinrose and Soumei Hoshino

Description: Two American boys, both obsessed with computer games and manga, find themselves in Tokyo and unable to get home. Adventures ensue!
Title: MEGATOKYO, VOL. 6
Author: Fred Gallagher

Description: This collected edition has 624 pages of samurai action.
Title: VAGABOND, VOL. 8 (VIZBIG EDITION)
Author: Takehiko Inoue

Description: Naruto learns more secrets from his past and moves closer to discovering the identity of his nemesis, Pain.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 47
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: These 560 pages collect volumes 22-24 of the Dragon Ball Z series.
Title: DRAGON BALL Z, VOL. 8 (VIZBIG EDITION)
Author: Akira Toriyama

Description: In the final volume of the spinoff series, Yugi must duel to the death to save Anzu’s soul.
Title: YU-GI-OH! R, VOL. 5
Author: Akira Ito
